fields.label: General
fields.name: general
fields.default: -General: Well Developed, well nourished and in no acute distress. Appropriately groomed.

fields.label: Head, Eyes, Ears, Nose, and Throat
fields.name: head_eyes_ears_nose_and_throat_
fields.default:
-Head: Normocephalic and atraumatic, no tenderness or masses.
-Eyes: Pupils are equal, round, and reactive to light. Extraocular movements are intact.
-Ears: Bilateral tympanic membranes are pearly gray, no signs of inflammation or effusion.
-Nose: Nasal septum midline, no epistaxis or discharge.
-Throat: Oropharynx clear, tonsils non-enlarged.

fields.label: Cardiovascular:
fields.name: cardiovascular
fields.default:
-Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, gallops, or rubs.
-Capillary refill < 2 seconds.
-Peripheral pulses are 2+ and equal bilaterally palpated at the carotid, radial, dorsalis pedis and posterior tibilais.
-No edema in extremities.

fields.label: Respiratory
fields.name: respiratory_
fields.default:
-Clear and equal breath sounds bilaterally, no wheezing, rales, or rhonchi.
-Respiratory effort even, no use of accessory muscles.
-Chest expansion symmetric.

fields.label: Gastrointestinal
fields.name: gastrointestinal
fields.default:
-Abdomen is soft, non-tender, and non-distended.
-Bowel sounds present in all four quadrants.
-No masses or hepatosplenomegaly.

fields.label: MSK
fields.name: msk
fields.default:
-Joint: No joint swelling, erythema, effusion, tenderness or deformity. 
-Lift/Carry: Examinee was able to lift, carry and handle light objects. 
-Squat: Examinee was able to squat and rise from that position, but with discomfort. 
-Sit to Rise: Examinee was able to rise from a sitting position without assistance and had no difficult getting up and down from the exam table. 
-Assist devices: N/A

fields.label: Neurological
fields.name: neurological
fields.default:
-Orientation: Alert and oriented x 4. (Person, Place, Time, Situation). 
-Behavior: Appropriate.  
-Mood/affect: Appropriate with congruent affect.
-Cranial nerves: II-XII intact. Hearing and speech are normal.
-Fine and gross manipulative skills are 10/10 with the right hand and 10/10 with the left hand. 
-R. Dominant. Can pinch, grasp, write and manipulate small object. Can reach overhead, anteriorly, and laterally. 
-Cerebellar Function: WNL, Romberg is negative. 
-Sensation: No numbness to light touch in the Face, upper or lower extremities. 
-Gain/Ambulation: Gait is normal. 
-Maneuvers: Gets on and off the exam table without difficult. Cannot walk on heels and toes and in tandem can squat and bend over to touch toes. 
-SLR: Sitting and Supine Straight leg raise are negative bilaterally.

fields.label: Assessment
fields.name: assessment
fields.default:
The claimant cooperated well and gave their best effort for the exam. 

Summary of Findings and Limitations: 
The claimant has limitations with respect to the following in an 8-hour workday. 

Sitting:  No restrictions or limitations. 

Standing/Walking: No restrictions or limitations. 

Lifting/Reaching/Handling: No restrictions or limitations. 

Memory: No restrictions or limitations. 

Vision/Hearing: No restrictions or limitations. 

Other: The claimant's alleged symptoms and their severity are consistent with the objective findings and/or observations, indicated within this report.

Please note that at the time of this report, there is no doctor-patient therapeutic relationship. All conclusions are advisory only, independently developed by the author, and are based upon the best professional judgment considering all data available at the time of preparation of this report. All opinions and conclusions are based upon a reasonable degree of professional judgment, as absolute predictions are not possible.
